{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1428","published":"2025-04-18T13:49:38Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:22.493723Z","upstream":["CVE-2025-2588"],"summary":"augeas security update","details":"Augeas is a configuration editing tool. It parses configuration files in their native\nformats and transforms them into a tree. Configuration changes are made by manipulating\nthis tree and saving it back into native config files.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA vulnerability has been found in Hercules Augeas 1.14.1 and classified as problematic. This vulnerability affects the function re_case_expand of the file src/fa.c. The manipulation of the argument re leads to null pointer dereference. Attacking locally is a requirement. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.(CVE-2025-2588)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"augeas","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/augeas&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["augeas-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","augeas-debuginfo-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","augeas-debugsource-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm","augeas-devel-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["augeas-help-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["augeas-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["augeas-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","augeas-debuginfo-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","augeas-debugsource-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm","augeas-devel-1.14.1-2.oe2403sp1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2025-1428.json"}},{"package":{"name":"augeas","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP4","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/augeas&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.12.0-8.oe2003sp4"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["augeas-1.12.0-8.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","augeas-debuginfo-1.12.0-8.oe2003sp4.aarc